    ```javascript
function alphabet_position_sum(s, k) {
    let sum = 0;
    for (let c of s) {
        sum += c.charCodeAt(0) - 'a'.charCodeAt(0) + 1;
    }
    for (let i = 0; i < k; i++) {
        let new_sum = 0;
        while (sum > 0) {
            new_sum += sum % 10;
            sum = Math.floor(sum / 10);
        }
        sum = new_sum;
    }
    return sum;
}
```

    1. Calculate the initial sum by iterating through each character in the string and adding the position of the letter in the alphabet to the sum. The position can be determined by subtracting the ASCII value of 'a' from the character's ASCII value and adding 1 (`c - 'a' + 1`).
2. For `k` number of times, perform the "transform operation" by setting the sum to the sum of its individual digits. This is done by iterating through the number while it's greater than zero, adding the remainder of the number divided by 10 (which gives the last digit) to a new sum variable, and then dividing the number by 10 to remove the last digit. After the loop is done, set the sum variable to the new sum.
3. Return the resulting integer.

